Secondly, Depth, God in the fleſh, that is, the Godhead not abſolutely conſidered, but as perſonally reſtrained to the Sonne; and to him not ſimply neither, as he is God, but as a Perſon ſubſiſting in the Godhead. The Word was made fleſh, ſaith S. John, that is, the ſecond Perſon; 
                     〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉
                  , The Word of God: who, as wee begat words out of our thoughts, beget his Sonne out of himſelfe, as it were by thinking within himſelfe an eternall Generation.

The workes of Chriſt are of two ſorts;

                     Anſw.
                   firſt, incommunicable; ſecondly, communicable.

Fifthly, Chriſt walked in the Light; and this, a three-fold Light: firſt, in the puritie of his Nature; there was no darkeneſſe in him at all; 

                     〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉
                  , none at all: in his minde, no darkeneſſe of ignorance; in his will and affections, no darkeneſſe of diſorder: ſecondly, in the light and puritie of holy converſation; hee never committed any workes of darkeneſſe: thirdly, in communion and fellowſhip with his Father, who dwells in Light inacceſſible.
